<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="39" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Shell oblique-heliciform, and translucent. Longitudinal furrows present behind apertural lip. Apertural dentition usually consists of two parietal, one palatal, one basal and one columellar lamella, and upper palatal and supracolumellar lamellae may be present. Genitalia with long and slender penis, penial sheath thin and not extending the entire penis length. Penial hooks dense, pale brown, expanded at base, with pointed tips, located on penial papillae, and curved towards genital orifice. Vaginal hooks may be present.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="39" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Celastraceae" genus="Perrotettia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Perrotettia" order="Celastrales" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Perrotettia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pfeiffer" authorityYear="1856" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptaxidae" genus="Discartemon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Discartemon" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Discartemon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are generally similar in having complex apertural dentition; however, their shell morphology is obviously different. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kobelt" authorityYear="1905" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptaxidae" genus="Perrottetia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Perrottetia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Perrottetia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a sub-heliciform shell, smaller size, last whorl rounded and more or less deflected, and mostly with two parietal lamellae. Although parietal, palatal, basal and columellar lamellae are always present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kobelt" authorityYear="1905" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptaxidae" genus="Perrottetia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Perrottetia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Perrottetia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, possession of second parietal, upper palatal and supracolumellar lamellae is variable, as is the presence of bifid lamellae (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.287.4572" author="Siriboon, T" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="41 - 57" refId="B75" refString="Siriboon, T, Sutcharit, C, Naggs, F, Panha, S, 2013. Three new species of the carnivorous snail genus Perrottetia Kobelt, 1905 from Thailand (Pulmonata, Streptaxidae). ZooKeys 287: 41 - 57, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.287.4572" title="Three new species of the carnivorous snail genus Perrottetia Kobelt, 1905 from Thailand (Pulmonata, Streptaxidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.287.4572" volume="287" year="2013">Siriboon et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.589.7933" author="Inkhavilay, K" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="23 - 53" refId="B35" refString="Inkhavilay, K, Siriboon, T, Sutcharit, C, Rowson, B, Panha, S, 2016. The first revision of the carnivorous land snail family Streptaxidae in Laos, with description of three new species (Pulmonata, Stylommatophora, Streptaxidae). ZooKeys 589: 23 - 53, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.589.7933" title="The first revision of the carnivorous land snail family Streptaxidae in Laos, with description of three new species (Pulmonata, Stylommatophora, Streptaxidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.589.7933" volume="589" year="2016">Inkhavilay et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.35885/ruthenica.2019.29(2).2" author="Bui, TC" journalOrPublisher="Ruthenica:" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="87 - 94" refId="B13" refString="Bui, TC, Do, VN, Ngo, DC, Do, DS, 2019. The land snail family Streptaxidae J. Gray, 1860 from Thua Thien Hue, Vietnam, with description of two new species (Gastropoda: Pulmonata). Ruthenica : 29 (2): 87 - 94, DOI: https://doi.org/10.35885/ruthenica.2019.29(2).2" title="The land snail family Streptaxidae J. Gray, 1860 from Thua Thien Hue, Vietnam, with description of two new species (Gastropoda: Pulmonata)." url="https://doi.org/10.35885/ruthenica.2019.29(2).2" volume="29" year="2019">Bui et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
). In contrast, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pfeiffer" authorityYear="1856" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptaxidae" genus="Discartemon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Discartemon" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Discartemon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
exhibits flattened to globose-heliciform shells, last whorl rounded to angular and less deflected with, usually, one parietal lamella.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">
Nonetheless, some 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pfeiffer" authorityYear="1856" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptaxidae" genus="Discartemon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Discartemon" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Discartemon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species from Thailand have two parietal lamellae, for example, 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. afthonodontia" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" rank="species" species="afthonodontia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">D. afthonodontia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.401.7075" author="Siriboon, T" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="45 - 107" refId="B76" refString="Siriboon, T, Sutcharit, C, Naggs, F, Rowson, B, Panha, S, 2014a. Revision of the carnivorous snail genus Discartemon Pfeiffer, 1856, with description of twelve new species (Pulmonata, Streptaxidae). ZooKeys 401: 45 - 107, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.401.7075" title="Revision of the carnivorous snail genus Discartemon Pfeiffer, 1856, with description of twelve new species (Pulmonata, Streptaxidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.401.7075" volume="401" year="2014 a">Siriboon et al. 2014a</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 7a, b) and 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. flavacandida" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" rank="species" species="flavacandida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">D. flavacandida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.401.7075" author="Siriboon, T" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="45 - 107" refId="B76" refString="Siriboon, T, Sutcharit, C, Naggs, F, Rowson, B, Panha, S, 2014a. Revision of the carnivorous snail genus Discartemon Pfeiffer, 1856, with description of twelve new species (Pulmonata, Streptaxidae). ZooKeys 401: 45 - 107, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.401.7075" title="Revision of the carnivorous snail genus Discartemon Pfeiffer, 1856, with description of twelve new species (Pulmonata, Streptaxidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.401.7075" volume="401" year="2014 a">Siriboon et al. 2014a</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 7e, f). Likewise, some 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kobelt" authorityYear="1905" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptaxidae" genus="Perrottetia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Perrottetia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Perrottetia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are also described with only a single parietal lamella, for example, the Vietnamese species 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. aberrata" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" rank="species" species="aberrata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">P. aberrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Souleyet, 1852) and 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. namdongensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" rank="species" species="namdongensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">P. namdongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bui &amp; Do, 2019 (see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.35885/ruthenica.2019.29(2).2" author="Bui, TC" journalOrPublisher="Ruthenica:" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="87 - 94" refId="B13" refString="Bui, TC, Do, VN, Ngo, DC, Do, DS, 2019. The land snail family Streptaxidae J. Gray, 1860 from Thua Thien Hue, Vietnam, with description of two new species (Gastropoda: Pulmonata). Ruthenica : 29 (2): 87 - 94, DOI: https://doi.org/10.35885/ruthenica.2019.29(2).2" title="The land snail family Streptaxidae J. Gray, 1860 from Thua Thien Hue, Vietnam, with description of two new species (Gastropoda: Pulmonata)." url="https://doi.org/10.35885/ruthenica.2019.29(2).2" volume="29" year="2019">Bui et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
: figs 2c-e, 3a-c), and the Laos species 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. unidentata" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" rank="species" species="unidentata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">P. unidentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Inkhavilay &amp; Panha, 2016 (see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.589.7933" author="Inkhavilay, K" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="23 - 53" refId="B35" refString="Inkhavilay, K, Siriboon, T, Sutcharit, C, Rowson, B, Panha, S, 2016. The first revision of the carnivorous land snail family Streptaxidae in Laos, with description of three new species (Pulmonata, Stylommatophora, Streptaxidae). ZooKeys 589: 23 - 53, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.589.7933" title="The first revision of the carnivorous land snail family Streptaxidae in Laos, with description of three new species (Pulmonata, Stylommatophora, Streptaxidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.589.7933" volume="589" year="2016">Inkhavilay et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 5f-i).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">
At present, the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kobelt" authorityYear="1905" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptaxidae" genus="Perrottetia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Perrottetia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Perrottetia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is comprised of about 30 nominal species distributed from India and Sri Lanka to Indochina and southern China (
